'From Squeak 2.4b of April 23, 1999 on 10 May 1999 at 3:14:03 pm'!"Change Set:		MsgTallyRecoverDate:			10 May 1999Author:			Dan IngallsCancels MessageTally interrupt process if you get an error while tallying.Otherwise, things get messy.  Suggested by Andres Valloud."!!Debugger methodsFor: 'private' stamp: 'di 5/10/1999 14:01'!process: aProcess controller: aController context: aContext	super initialize.	Smalltalk at: #MessageTally ifPresent: [:c | c new close].	contents _ nil. 	interruptedProcess _ aProcess.	interruptedController _ aController.	contextStackTop _ aContext.	self newStack: (contextStackTop stackOfSize: 1).	contextStackIndex _ 1.	externalInterrupt _ false.	selectingPC _ true! !